<h2>
    Introduction: Why Bend Is a World-Class Fishing Destination
</h2>
<p>
    Located in the heart of Central Oregon, <strong>Bend</strong> is surrounded by a stunning variety of rivers, lakes, and reservoirs—making it one of the most diverse and scenic fishing regions in the Pacific Northwest. From the powerful flows of the Deschutes River to the serene alpine lakes of the Cascade Lakes Highway, anglers here can target <strong>rainbow, brown, brook trout, kokanee, and even largemouth bass</strong>—all within an hour’s drive.
</p>
<h2>
    Fish Species You’ll Find Around Bend
</h2>
<p>
    Bend’s cool waters are home to:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Rainbow Trout</strong> – Native and stocked in most rivers and lakes.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Brown Trout</strong> – Common in Wickiup, Crooked, and East Lake.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Brook Trout</strong> – High-elevation streams and lakes.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Kokanee Salmon</strong> – Schooling fish in reservoirs.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Largemouth Bass</strong> – In Crane Prairie and some warmer lakes.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Mountain Whitefish</strong> – Often caught in tailwaters like the Crooked.
    </li>
</ul>
