<h2>
    Fly Fishing Near Bend
</h2>
<p>
    Fly anglers flock to Bend for:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Dry fly hatches</strong> on Fall, Metolius, and Upper Deschutes.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Euro nymphing</strong> on Crooked and Lower Deschutes.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Top flies</strong>: Elk Hair Caddis, BWO, Zebra Midge, Prince Nymph, Chubby Chernobyl.
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    Bring a 4–6 wt rod, floating line, and long leaders for spooky trout.
</p>
<h2>
    Spin and Bait Fishing in Bend’s Waters
</h2>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>Allowed in most lakes</strong> and some river sections (check regs).
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Effective lures</strong>: Rooster Tails, Kastmasters, Thomas Buoyant.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Bait</strong>: PowerBait, worms, corn (for kokanee), salmon eggs.
    </li>
    <li>
        Trolling is popular on East, Wickiup, and Crane Prairie.
    </li>
</ul>
<h2>
    Ice Fishing Near Bend (Winter Opportunities)
</h2>
<p>
    When the snow falls, head to:
</p>
<ul>
    <li>
        <strong>East Lake</strong>: Ice fishing for rainbows and kokanee.
    </li>
    <li>
        <strong>Wickiup</strong>: Deeper water makes for good mid-winter ice fishing.
    </li>
</ul>
<p>
    Bring safety gear, augers, and check conditions with ODFW before going.
</p>
